# CODEOWNERS — review routing for VIATOR / OpenJourneyPlanner.
#
# Every PR needs at minimum the matching owner's review (per branch
# protection on main). For a single-operator project today, that's
# `@TOP-PHE` on everything. As the team grows, narrow these globs to
# delegate by area.
#
# Audit-2026-05 #11. See https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-security/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners

# ─────────────────────── default ───────────────────────
*                                @TOP-PHE

# ─────────────────────── high-trust paths ──────────────
# Anything that affects security, supply chain, or runtime container
# behaviour gets explicit attention even when the default owner is the
# same — the explicit rule reminds reviewers to slow down on these.

/.github/                        @TOP-PHE
/.github/workflows/              @TOP-PHE
/.github/dependabot.yml          @TOP-PHE
/docker/                         @TOP-PHE
/.trivyignore                    @TOP-PHE
/sonar-project.properties        @TOP-PHE
/.pre-commit-config.yaml         @TOP-PHE
/pyproject.toml                  @TOP-PHE
/requirements.txt                @TOP-PHE
/requirements-dev.txt            @TOP-PHE
/alembic/                        @TOP-PHE

# ─────────────────────── audit & docs ──────────────────
# Audit doc + admin-guide are operational source-of-truth; changes
# should be deliberate and reviewed in the same PR as their code change.
/docs/audit-2026-05.md           @TOP-PHE
/docs/admin-guide.md             @TOP-PHE
